blog.description: My name's Memory, and I'm a multifandom blog! My series are Fire Emblem, Pokemon, My Hero Academia, LOZ, DR, Overwatch, P3, MM, Stardew Valley, Death Mark and a few others! Love letter rqs are closed! Ask count: 32 [icon by the lovely ncwi! 💕]

summary: If it’s not too much to ask, can I request a love letter from Red from Pokémon? Ignore this if you don’t want to or if requests...
question: If it’s not too much to ask, can I request a love letter from Red from Pokémon? Ignore this if you don’t want to or if requests are closed, I just noticed you haven’t done much for Pokémon and as much as I ADORE your Fire Emblem stuff I think the Pokémon trainers need more love. Also the idea of Red writing letters to his crush or s/o from whatever long distance he goes to train is cute! I usually nickname myself Teal when I play the games but feel free to use any name you want.
answer:
!!! this was really fun!!!! thank you, i hope you like it!!! and honestly i feel the same, i love writing for the pokemon trainers so hopefully i can do more in the future!!! 💕

Hey Teal,

I know it’s been awhile since I sent off a letter–I hope you’re not too upset. Though, if it means you’ll be making that cute, annoyed face while you read this, it might be a little hard to regret it. 

And I know you’ve been curious about Alola, so I hope the pictures I enclosed show you a little glimpse of some of my adventures here. The trainers are strong, and the pokemon are unlike any I’ve ever seen…I’ll send you some of my pokedex data once I get back to Hau’oli, so you can see them. Tell me which one is your favourite…and I’ll see about catching it to bring back home to you.

You know…I really miss you. It’s great and all, meeting new people and seeing new sights–but my mind keeps wandering back to you, all the time. Hey, once I visit home, why don’t you come with me this time? I want to show you the beauty of Alola…and we can go to all the places I traveled when I was young. Johto, Hoenn, Kalos, Unova, wherever you want, I’ll take you. 

Anyways, I’ll be looking forward to coming home again. And hopefully, this time we can leave side by side–or with your hand in mine, if you prefer.

Red
